                             @{b}@{u} NEW FEATURES @{ub}@{uu}
                             

     If you have played WtW (Wålly the Wörrm) you probably know what this is 
     all about and then you don't have to read ALL of this boring manual.
     So... this is what you need to know:
     
     W2 is very similar to WtW but with a few changes (surprise, surprice)!
     The changes are (in no particular order):
     
     @{fg highlight}*@{fg text}    @{" Four new levels " Link "The levels"} Wow! ;-)
     *    4 tunes to every level.
     @{fg highlight}*@{fg text}    3 flashing "items" at the same time
     *    Cool teleporters.
     @{fg highlight}*@{fg text}    @{" Action items. " Link "The items"} Be careful when you take theese items.
     *    OneWay-doors.
     @{fg highlight}*@{fg text}    New cool "Pinball-like" scoreboard.
     *    64 colours instead of 32  (sory we couldn't make it in AGA)
     @{fg highlight}*@{fg text}    @{" TWO-PLAYER MODE !! " Link "Two-player"} (May the best worm win)
     *    Three different speed levels instead of just two.  ;-)
     @{fg highlight}*@{fg text}    Ability to load other levels.
     *    @{" Make your own levels " Link "Userlevels"}
     @{fg highlight}*@{fg text}    Animated "items" to pick up.
     *    Flashing colours on the levels to bring them to life.
     @{fg highlight}*@{fg text}    No long anoying "got-new-hiscore" intro anymore.
     *    Two different Start-positions. (Random selection)     
     @{fg highlight}*@{fg text}    TWO different @{" 2-Ply modes! " Link "Two-player"}( F3 = Snake mode )

     This is what i can remember at the time... ;-)
     
     Other things that could be "good to know" before you start is:
     
     * The @{" background story. " Link "Introduction"} (short "intro" story)
     * And the @{" hotkeys. " Link "Hotkeys"} (Scoreboard features etc.)
     @{fg highlight}* NOTE!@{fg text}
       When playing 2-ply the "start-positions" will be selected RANDOMLY!
       The object of the 2-ply mode is to get the other player killed!
     * Also read about the @{" Action Items. " Link "The items"}

     @{b}Ok!@{ub} Now you can go back to @{" Main menu " Link "Main"}.

@EndNode

