                             @{b}@{u} The "Items" @{ub}@{uu}


     There is three items on the level at the same time.
     
     Here's a table of what happens when you take the different
     "items", how many points you'll get and how much longer you will be!
     
     @{fg highlight}NOTE! @{fg text}Some colours are only available in either 1 or 2-ply mode!
     "Stays" = How many pixels you can go before the item disappear!
     "Mode"  = In which mode ( 1Ply / 2Ply ) that the item is available!
     

     @{u}Colour  Mode  Points  Length  Stays  What happens!@{uu}
     
@{fg highlight}     Blue     1     750       8     600   Changes your direction randomly.@{fg text}
     Red      2      -       10     500   Freezes your opponent 4 a while.
@{fg highlight}     Orange   2      -       10     500   Changes direction of your enemy.@{fg text}
     Green   1&2    900       9     550   Dig under the ground 4 a while.
@{fg highlight}     Yellow  1&2    650      10     650   Nothing !!@{fg text}
     Pink    1&2    500      12     650   Nothing !!
@{fg highlight}     Grey    1&2    400      20     450   Nothing !!@{fg text}
     
@{fg highlight}     NOTE! @{fg text}If you don't take any items you will get 1 pixel longer every
     30 pixel you go! you will also get 1 point every pixel you move forward!
     
     Ok! I hope You'll notice that some items are better than others.
     And also that it's actually better to just be winding around than to
     take the GREY items. (you'll get more points and less length!)
     
     In 2-Ply mode on the other hand, it can be good to take the grey items.
     Because the longer you are the harder it gets for your opponent!
     The same things goes for the yellow and pink items: in 1-ply mode they
     are both good, although the yellow is better. And in 2-ply mode the
     pink item will probably be better!
     
     @{fg highlight}The GREEN items @{fg text}can be very useful and dangerous! They will make you
     go under ground for about 20 pixels. Using green items you can go under
     walls and under yourself or your enemy. The danger is that you might be
     directly under a wall when Wålly heads for the surface again = dead!
     
@{fg highlight}     Knowing theese things will give you an advantage over your friends ;-)@{fg text}

     @{" Main menu " Link "Main"}.

