                             @{b}@{u} Name & Music @{ub}@{uu}

     When you have made the two pictures. (Map and Level)
     You have to pack them. You can do this with the program included.
     The files will be named "something.M" and "something.B".
     Where "something" is the name of the level.
     This is the text that will show up in the game!

     If you want the level to be called "BananaWorld" in the game, you
     should name the files "BananaWorld.M" and "BananaWorld.B".
     Although this will be taken care of by the packing program :-)

     If you want to have music to your level you have to make this in
     Med format. the music file should be named "BananaWorld.tune".
     if you want the music to change when you die etc. you have to do
     a multisong (MED). It should include 4 songs:

     1=Intro.   2=While Playing.     3=Killed.       4=Highscore.

     Pictures and songs should all be placed in the X_Levels drawer.

@EndNode
